# iba-ai-automation-guard

> **AI can now do all of this. Did anyone authorize it?**

---

## The Problem

AI can now:

- Write your content
- Build your website
- Handle your customer service
- Create your product
- Run your marketing

Every one of these is an autonomous agent acting on your behalf.

None of them have a pre-execution authorization gate.

No declared scope. No hard limits. No kill threshold. No human principal signature. No audit chain.

The agent does what it can do — not what you authorized it to do.

---

## The Five Gaps

| Capability | What the agent can do | What you authorized |
|-----------|----------------------|-------------------|
| Write content | Any topic · Any platform · Any audience · Any claim | "Write a blog post about X" |
| Build website | Any code · Any deployment · Any endpoint · Production push | "Build me a landing page" |
| Customer service | Any response · Any commitment · Any refund · Any promise | "Handle support tickets" |
| Create product | Any feature · Any dependency · Any external API · Any release | "Build this feature" |
| Run marketing | Any channel · Any spend · Any audience · Any message | "Run our marketing" |

The gap between what you said and what the agent can do is not a bug.

**It is the architecture.**

---

## The IBA Layer

A signed intent certificate closes the gap before the agent acts.

### Content Writing
```json
{
  "intent": "Write weekly blog posts on AI governance",
  "scope": ["blog_write", "draft_publish"],
  "forbidden": ["social_post", "email_send", "external_publish"],
  "limits": {
    "topics": "AI governance only",
    "tone": "professional",
    "kill_threshold": "any_claim_about_competitors"
  },
  "signature": "ed25519:..."
}
```

### Website Building
```json
{
  "intent": "Build landing page for product launch",
  "scope": ["repo_read", "branch_write", "staging_deploy"],
  "forbidden": ["production_deploy", "external_api_call", "payment_integration"],
  "limits": {
    "repository": "marketing-site only",
    "kill_threshold": "any_production_touch"
  },
  "signature": "ed25519:..."
}
```

### Customer Service
```json
{
  "intent": "Handle tier-1 support tickets",
  "scope": ["ticket_read", "ticket_respond", "kb_read"],
  "forbidden": ["refund_issue", "account_modify", "escalation_bypass"],
  "limits": {
    "response_type": "information only",
    "kill_threshold": "any_financial_commitment"
  },
  "signature": "ed25519:..."
}
```

### Product Creation
```json
{
  "intent": "Implement user authentication feature",
  "scope": ["repo_read", "branch_write", "test_execute"],
  "forbidden": ["production_deploy", "dependency_add", "secret_access"],
  "limits": {
    "repository": "auth-service only",
    "kill_threshold": "any_external_api · any_production_touch"
  },
  "signature": "ed25519:..."
}
```

### Marketing
```json
{
  "intent": "Run paid social campaign for April launch",
  "scope": ["campaign_create", "ad_publish", "analytics_read"],
  "forbidden": ["budget_increase", "new_channel", "audience_expand"],
  "limits": {
    "budget_usd": 5000,
    "channels": "LinkedIn · Twitter only",
    "kill_threshold": "any_spend_above_5000"
  },
  "signature": "ed25519:..."
}
```

---

## Gate Logic

```
Certificate valid?              → PROCEED
Action outside declared scope?  → BLOCK
Hard limit exceeded?            → BLOCK
Forbidden action attempted?     → BLOCK
Kill threshold triggered?       → TERMINATE + LOG
No certificate present?         → BLOCK
```

**No cert = No execution.**

The agent cannot write outside its declared topic.
The agent cannot deploy to production without a cert that permits it.
The agent cannot issue a refund without a cert that declares it.
The agent cannot spend above the declared limit.
The agent cannot remove the gate that governs it.

